  "market_context": "Daily price action in YM1! during May–June 2023, showing a sequence of trend continuation and reversal attempts where the analyst uses previous day high (PDH) and previous day low (PDL) as dynamic bias and liquidity targets.",
  "key_observation": "Price consistently reaches for the previous day’s high or low; failure to close beyond those levels frames reversals, while successful displacement confirms continuation bias.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the previous day high (PDH) and previous day low (PDL) as primary liquidity and bias reference points.",
    "Step 2: Observe whether price closes above PDH (bullish bias, draw on next PDH) or fails to close above (bearish reversal setup off PDH).",
    "Step 3: When price sweeps PDL but cannot close below it, anticipate a move toward the next PDH; when it closes below PDL, shift bias to short and target next PDL.",
    "Step 4: Track sequential displacement: after taking one side (e.g., PDH), expect price to reach for the opposite side (PDL) unless consolidation occurs.",
    "Step 5: Use failed displacements (wick through but close back inside range) at PDH/PDL as reversal triggers, confirming with candle closure inside prior range."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Previous day high/low are not static levels but dynamic draw-on-liquidity zones that alternate as bias anchors. Price tends to oscillate between them until a structural break occurs; reversals are confirmed by failure to displace and close back inside range.",
